text: <https://archidekt.com/decks/145949#Archetune-Up_Shanna>

Hey everyone, I’m driving 5 hours home, and I need a bit of help on my next article. I need to make some cuts to a Shanna deck I’m tuning up, and since I’m clueless when it comes to G/W. I’ve hit the relevant Themes on the site that I want to go over and talk about, I just have a bunch of suggestions and additions too, and I’m not sure where to trim the fat.

The only stipulation is that they want to keep in Huatli and Monastery Mentor, so I tried to keep those in mind when putting the cards together. Any thoughts would be greatly appreciated. I’ll check in and try and talk a bit whenever I get to any test stops. :grin:
I’m just worried about any glaring flaws or omissions :cold_sweat:
Service is super spotty for me rn, but I'll take a look later!
What do you think about trading Benalish for the new Commander Enchantment?
Shanna is a 2 drop, good chance you can cast her 4 times in a game and give +4/+4 instead of just +1/+1
Most of your tokens are 1/1s? [[!mentor of the Meek]]
Oh shit, I forgot to even look at the cards from the Populate deck. Heck!

That enchantment seems HOT in this deck. That’s a good call, Seth. 

I forgot if I cut Mentor it if it wasn’t included. I think the anthems may impact its usefulness. Green card draw may just be better in this situation? Most token decks can’t use Rishkar’s Expertise, but this one can
Yeah, if you play anthems mentor is really not as good, and given that a lot of the times there's no mana to spare for his ability anyway...
Massively disagree with that second part, but I do agree with the anthem bit
[[!Beast Whisperer]]
Yeah, there's like 30 creatures here, Whisperer works XD
Beast Whisperer is good, as well as Guardian Project, but I was going to wait a bit to see where the list shakes out to see if I have more creature based token makers or not.
I have to cut 27 cards though xD
Maybe I’ll cut 27 creatures...:thinking_face:
Oh, I thought it looked like a long list... I'm not used to this layout, I didn't see the number in the upper left
Sorry xD yeah. I have to cut, which I why I wanted some opinions. I’m worried I may be using spells that really on over extending too much or things like that
I’m a bit out of my element. Matt helped me a bunch when figuring out cards to swap with the original deck

My suggestions for cuts:

• Pathbreaker Ibex: Without haste, the chances you'll get to use his ability are a little slight to be spending 6 mana on.
• Darien, King of Kjeldor: Given that you have tokens, you'll have blockers much of the time to dissuade attackers, and you'd probably be better served to just have another guaranteed token producer.
• Venerated Loxodon: I... really just am not much of a fan of this guy.
• God-Eternal Oketra: Great in most creature decks, however with it being a cast trigger it doesn't do anything with a substantial amount of your token producers.

• Genesis: Kinda the same thing as Oketra here.
• Dictate of Heliod: 5 mana for +2/+2 is just a lot, imo.
• Ant Queen: I like this card as a mana sink, but I'm not sure I see enough mana with which to sink?
• Harmonize: Usually a huge fan of this card, but I think the effects based on power/amount of creatures work better for you here.
• From Beyond: I love this card, but I don't see any Eldrazi to search for?
I think From Beyond is for the sake of the weenies that are mana

• Conclave Tribunal: In budget builds this is a great card, but honestly even if you can convoke it out its still not as good as path/swords.
• Bramble Sovereign: I've unfortunately tried to include and ended up cutting this card in every green deck I've played, including my oops all creatures. Having two extra mana is just hard to come by, and you again have a lot of non-creature token makers, diminishing its value even further.
• Armageddon: I would, but I also understand why others wouldn't.
• Mentor of the Meek: It is in here, but I would still cut it for the reasons I described above
Agreed DM, I was more trying to say I'd either cut it or add an Eldrazi.
Otherwise, its just a worse Awakening Zone
How do you not normally have some mana up for interaction? 2 shouldn't be that bad, especially in mid-to-late game
For interaction, sure. Bramble Sovereign isn't interaction, though. You have to spend it when you cast the spell.

• Benalish Marshall: WWW is a lot of white.
• Talisman of Unity: You're playing all the rampant growths and all of the mana dorks, I think this is overkill.
• Krosan Grip: You have a lot of enchantment/artifact removal that does something extra for the deck. If you're playing against a lot of combo, this is still a must, but if not then I'd say you can skip on it for cheaper/more relevant removal.
I pulled a foil Bramble Sovereign in my battlebond box, so I really wanted to like it. I just... don't. It was feel bads every time I drew it.

A few reasons for certain things

-Darien is in there because if I recall correctly, they had some soul sisters originally, and they synergize well. If I cut Darien, should I cut them as well?

-Oketra and Genesis are in a similar vein as Beast Whisperer. If I end up running more cards like Nest Invader to put a body or two on board, they get better. If not, I won’t have an issue cutting them. It just depends on the final decklist

-Harmonize is in there because I feel like Rishkar’s Expertise and Shamanic Rev can be a bit trick if you’re behind. Harmonize always will draw you three cards, and us less feast or famine than the others.
Soul sisters?
gain life when creature etb
The other suggestions are reasonable I think, I’ll just have to look through them again later, but they were super helpful

Gotcha
That's a reasonable reason to keep Harmonize. If you do then, I'd suggest cutting Camaraderie

Minus reasoning like "I don't own one and I don't want to buy one" or something
It's just the best removal

K-Grip is great in more powerful metas. In less powerful ones, it's just worse naturalize.
Beast Within isn't bad either, but even if you're not in a powerful meta, denying responses is still good
